{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"55423cca-2a14-40e9-9da4-c98142dd3b51","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped VSTest support by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk **3.8**, the default test runner switched to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (the new \"runner mode\"). In **4.x**, the legacy VSTest compatibility layer (`Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge`) is **no longer included**, so `vstest.console` can't discover tests at all.\n\n### Your options\n\n1. **Recommended — switch your CI to `dotnet test`**, which works natively with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n   ```\n   dotnet test TestProject.csproj\n   ```\n\n2. **If you must keep `vstest.console`**, re-enable the VSTest adapter by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsVSTestBridge>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\nOption 1 is the intended path forward — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the long-term replacement for VSTest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8840167a-1900-4cad-9245-1453ee553a39","outputTokens":260,"requestId":"0425:1423A3:1D685D1:2185552:69E836C8"},"id":"7b936086-6612-4952-8806-7b4cf3745fa5","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:47:43.206Z","parentId":"5b5768f1-0fef-43a4-a8ce-ae5ed0c9de0b"}
